what is the quality of the tables in the fitness database

The tables in the fitness database exhibit excellent data quality, with all analyzed columns having 100% non-null values except for the 'ResolutionDate' column in the 'ServiceTickets' table, which has 59% null values.

Key Observations

  • All tables ('Products', 'SaleDetails', 'ServiceTickets', 'Sales', and 'Customers') contain complete data in most columns, indicating a well-maintained database.
  • The 'ServiceTickets' table has a significant number of null values (59%) in the 'ResolutionDate' column, which may indicate incomplete information regarding ticket resolutions.
  • Data types appear appropriate for each column, using VARCHAR for text fields, INTEGER for IDs, DECIMAL for prices, and DATE/TIMESTAMP for dates.

The tables in the fitness database exhibit excellent data quality, with all analyzed columns having 100% non-null values except for the 'ResolutionDate' column in the 'ServiceTickets' table, which has 59% null values.

  • Data types appear appropriate for each column, using VARCHAR for text fields, INTEGER for IDs, DECIMAL for prices, and DATE/TIMESTAMP for dates.
